(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Petilil and Lilligant
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Petilil and Lilligant
body:
548: Petilil

And today, we get to see the obligatory addition for each generation, it seems. But even in the point of this “basic seedling-like Grass-type” trope, Petilil feels even more underwhelming than most of the others like it. It’s cute, but it’s not got one thing readily available to it to have it stand out as a Grass-type. I don’t dislike the trope altogether like I felt like I’ve given the impression of before, but I do feel lke Petilil collects most of the ire when I point out that Poke-trope as one of the more annoying things I find about Grass types.

Personal Score: 6/10

Petilil’s little more than alright. The words might be a bit harsh, but 6/10 feels appropriate.

549: Lilligant

Things do improve quite a bit with Lilligant. While it is a Pokemon that I wouldn’t be hurt, or feel like I’m missing out on something had it never existed, I do like it. It’s cute and elegant. I do like how the lower half of its body doesn’t have any legs, but rather it’s one big bulb with very tiny, yellow feet to move it around. While Serperior pulled it off better, I also like Lilligant’s rather royal look. Color scheme included.

Personal Score: 8/10

I do like it but… boy I’m struggling to come up with much to talk about it haha.

Overall:

Not an amazing line, but sure. Lilligant is just gonna be a fairly standard plant-humanoid and it’s gonna be really nice looking while it’s doing it. But we have had more extravagant plant-things in the past.
